Also today is @brianmejeur’s birthday. So welcome, new baby. And, happy birthday to the man who literally makes magic and creates incredible adventure into our lives. He dreams wild dreams, and then convinced me we can make them come true. And we do. You are an amazing father, an INCREDIBLE partner, and your life is a gift to me every single day. Feeling extra blessed by this life of ours today.

It’s been a very spacey and very podcasty past year. 

I have gotten to have the COOLEST conversations with space and clean tech organizations about new technology, leadership and hiring. 

Thrilled to have had the privilege of interviewing incredible guests on our ‘AdAstra With’ show, and to be a guest on the @payloadspace Pathfinder Podcast. 

Shout out to incredible leaders in the space industry who we’ve had as  guests on episodes released: Chris Thompson (SpaceX Founding Team, CTO @phantomspaceco), @zebulgar Delian Asparouhov (Cofounder @vardaspaceindustries, Principal @foundersfund), Thomas Cobbs (CoFounder COO Datum Source), THE Hans Koenigsmann @hanskoenigsmann (SpaceX Founding Member), Janeya Griffin @janeyagriffin (Founder @equityspacealliance
), Scott Macklin (Director of Engineering @graviticsinc ), Glenn Case (Founder & CTO @hermeuscorp), Josh Giegel @joshgiegel (Founder/CEO Gambit), and Ryan Carlisle (CoFounder & CTO Argo Space Corp).

Bumpdate 22.5 weeks: I have to check my app to know what week of pregnancy I am. I think I had about 22 bumpdate pictures by this point in Maezen’s pregnancy. So funny how different it is for my second child. 
•
In celebration of Mother’s Day coming up I want to share: a favorite pregnancy purchase, a favorite kids purchase, and a favorite pregnancy health staple + some sales. 
•
I want to LIVE in @blanqigirls leggings. They give me compression where I need them, they are buttery soft, and they give the perfect amount of support for my bump. These were a gift but I 100% would be sharing about them even if they weren’t. See a few ways I love to style them in the video & please admire my incredible transitions in the video. 
• 
•
@lovevery is a sustainable, Montessori-inspired play kit subscription you can get for kids depending on their ages. Not only does it teach you (the parent) how to relate to and educate your little one. Maezen is SO EXCITED to play with his Lovevery play sets. 
•
•
One pregnancy health staple: chiropractic and body work (like physical therapy and massage). Even with exercising every day, my body be ACHIN’. Going to a chiropractor who understands the pregnant body is a GAME changer and helps me understand how to move, breathe and exercise to support my body in this new shape. 
•
This last part is mostly a little diary check in for me. I’m somehow still feeling sick, like really sick. I have good days and bad days, but my goodness the nausea and vomiting is unreal. I’m also finally lifting out of a pretty gnarly depression that I was dealing with for the first few months of pregnancy. Wild how much that made me feel like not myself. Even with all of that, I love being pregnant. The feeling of baby kicking (almost spilled the gender there!), the knowing that we are growing our family, it’s so exciting to me. 
•

Adding another boy to the family 💙 🦖 ✈️ 🦕 🚌 🛻 ⚽️ 👶 🐶 🐮 

I was so sure this baby was a girl that I took TWO @sneakpeektest at-home gender tests, and was still thinking there was a chance at my anatomy ultrasound 😉

Maezen is so excited for his brother, and so are we. “Bus Muff” is the new baby’s affectionate name before he comes earthside. Maezen named him that based off two of his favorite things- buses and muffins!

As I get closer to the final trimester and the reality of a new baby sinks in I’m both terrified and so excited. It took me about a year to catch my balance, and feel like life was possible, after Maezen. 

Here is to our next adventure, presumably with even more airplanes, dinosaurs, busses, trucks, balls (lol), baby dolls, arts & crafts, obsessions with animals, and other toddler boy things. 

Huge shout out to my incredible husband who has been taking on so much more physical and mental load for our family so I can get some rest these days. Shout out to @blanqigirls - these leggings make me feel so comfortable when everything else makes me feel so awkward in this body. And shout out to the incredible @lovevery kits that give me educational games to play with Maezen, reducing my mental load and enhancing our relationship!

6 years of marriage?!?!?! This anniversary really snuck up on me. 

One toddler, one newborn coming soon, two rambunctious dogs, a home, a business, a cabin, a pilots license, a thriving family, a social life filled with incredible friends, SO much love and SO much growth. We have built such a beautiful life over these 6 years and I feel like the luckiest woman getting to love and partner with this man. 

Thank you for loving me so well, for learning who I am in all the vivid human detail, for sharing the depths of yourself with me, and for having SO much fun. It’s unreal how much I enjoy time with you, sweet husband. 

The 6th anniversary is traditionally the iron anniversary. In that tradition, this quote is beyond perfect, as we have sharpened and softened each other so much as we’ve grown together: “As iron sharpens iron, so one person sharpens another.” Proverbs 27:17. I am so lucky to be sharpened by you. 

Happy anniversary honey! Thank you for being my safe space, for teaching me how to adventure well, and trust enough to jump. 

Tonight Brian and Maezen and I are going out for a family celebration. Every week we summarize the things we have to celebrate as individuals and as a family. Monthly we go celebrate! This was our antidote to always adding more goals and not stopping to celebrate the completion of them. 

Loving you so gently and so fiercely is my biggest gift to celebrate, always.

✔️ Pilot 
✔️ Very pregnant pilot
✈️ Reminder: We can do hard things. 

Yesterday, with a 9.5 hour day at the airport, I passed my final checkride and earned my private pilots license. 

This past year of training has been wild. At many points it was joyfully exhilarating, and at many points I wanted to throw in the towel. Late nights, early mornings, learning topics that don’t come to me naturally, developing muscle memory while managing sufficient levels of cortisol, all while juggling the other very intense areas of life (family I’m obsessed with, running a really wonderful business, health, friendships that mean so much to me, making a baby…) and working hard to do them well. 

Keeping my eye on the finish line meant leaning on a lot of psychology tools and a powerhouse support team. 

Getting curious about problems, and getting creative with solutions. 

I wouldn’t say I /recommend/ doing something so intensive and demanding while pregnant, but I now can say it is possible. 

Huge thanks to my incredible husband who picked up much in our life to balance for me and gave me extra TLC,  to my sweet son whose excitement for “mama up-planes” made this all feel a little more possible, to my sweet mom who has celebrated every step of the way, for my incredible friends who supported me, to my remarkable team at work who often feel more like family, and for an airport of incredible pilots @flyitacademy who very quickly came to feel like close friends. 

We can do hard things. 

Thanks for the epic pictures @billypurta (but he’s a realtor so plz don’t contact him for photos even though he takes crazy good ones).

Why did I get my pilots license? Because my incredible husband, who has a bachelors and masters degree in aerospace, is literally a rocket scientist, and loves all things space-nerdy, really wanted to take to the skies. He gets migraines that take away his vision, so he couldn’t. But I could, so I did. Now we can fly together and he can experience that piloty freedom. 

It’s a really incredible joy in life to have a partnership like this. Each of our wants and wins becomes the wants and wins of the other. I don’t just do everything he likes because I’m awesome - we just take taking care of each other and achieving dreams together really seriously…. Or really playfully….? We get to do big things together with this remarkable synergy! I feel lucky beyond words. 

If you went blind I’d be your eyes, and today, I’ll be your wings. ✈️ 

We’re in our final days as a family of 3. I was worried I was not cut out to be a mama when we first had Maezen. Now I understand motherhood as one of the most beautiful blessings and biggest callings I’ve ever had, alongside being a wife. 

As we anticipate baby number two, I’m both so excited for meeting this new soul and gently welcoming him (?, three gender tests and I’m still not sure he’ll be a boy) into the world. And I feel an overwhelming fear for how separate I may feel from my incredible guys who are already earthside, as I get consumed by the newborn needs. 

This life is big, this life is grand. Don’t forget to soak it all in my friends. 

One of the many fun things we’ve been enjoying as a family is the awesome new @lovevery music kit. It is so fun. Brand new product from Lovevery. #loveverygift

Welcome earthside precious little chonk. 

✨ Muzelo Jetson 🛩️ (pronounced “muse-low” because Maezen and I wanted another buddy who gets to spell their name for everyone we ever meet)

Another home birth - I went to hell and back again, all resulting in a perfectly healthy and thriving family. This little boy was born peaceful after a gentle arrival (for him). 

I was worried there was no way I could love another child nearly as much as I love Maezen. But it is true what they say… somehow your heart expands more than seems possible. 

Maezen appears to be the best brother ever. He loves his baby, holds him gently, and loves him deeply. 

BRB soaking up this newborn bliss and catching Zs wherever we can 😴 🥱
